{
  "stem": "8569.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother's response was that she lived through the first war, and she knows that surviving the war is hard, but after the war is even harder.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she wanted to stay where she was, to take care of our belongings and what have you, that the, quote, 'security' versus insecurity of going who knows where.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So she was adamant she's not going anywhere.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it was terrible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was absolutely terrible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My-- my mother just found it very, very difficult.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then my sister was adamant, and they-- they did leave.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we stayed on, and-- [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] then, of course-- the Germans-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The-- the repercussions and persecution of Jews started at that time.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At first-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] of course, we couldn't go to schools.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then there was a decree that the Jews-- I don't remember the exact order, but what happened was that the Jews could not live in certain parts of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Warsaw was declared into the Aryan side and the Jewish side.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So Jewish people who lived in the non-Jewish area had to move into the Jewish area.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then Jews--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived in a Jewish area all along, so luckily for us, we didn't have to move.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But many people did have, and they usually had a very short notice about leaving what they had and move, not knowing where.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Then the Jews were not allowed to have furs.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember going with my mother to a certain depot, where we had to leave our furs.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my sister and I had winter coats with fur collars.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So my mother took off the collars, and we brought it all to the depot.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
